# RabbitMQ Messaging Guidelines

## Publishing Messages
Use `IRabbitMqBus` to publish messages:
```csharp
await _messageBus.PublishAsync(message, "queue-name");
```

## Queue Names
Use kebab-case with domain prefix:
```csharp
private const string UpdateShortenPathQueue = "shorten-link.update";
```

## Consumer Setup
Implement `IHostedService` for background consumers:
```csharp
public class MyConsumer(IServiceProvider sp) : IHostedService
{
    public async Task StartAsync(CancellationToken cancellationToken)
    {
        var rabbitMqBus = sp.GetRequiredService<IRabbitMqBus>();
        var connection = await rabbitMqBus.CreateConnectionAsync();
        var channel = await connection.CreateChannelAsync();
        
        await channel.QueueDeclareAsync(
            queue: "queue-name",
            durable: true,
            exclusive: false,
            autoDelete: false);
    }
}
```

## Error Handling
Always use manual acknowledgment with retry:
```csharp
consumer.ReceivedAsync += async (model, ea) =>
{
    try
    {
        // Process message
        await channel.BasicAckAsync(ea.DeliveryTag, multiple: false);
    }
    catch (Exception ex)
    {
        // Requeue for retry
        await channel.BasicNackAsync(ea.DeliveryTag, multiple: false, requeue: true);
    }
};
```

## Scoped Services in Consumers
Create a scope when using scoped services:
```csharp
using var scope = sp.CreateScope();
var context = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<ApplicationDbContext>();
```
